%EDITMAC  ------------------ SHOWCUT2  MACRO  ------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
+THE%SHOWCUT2+MACRO IS USED TO SHOW THE FIRST LINE OF ALL "CUT" LINES.
+AN OPTIONAL PARM OF TERSE WILL PREVENT DISPLAY FOR CUT LEVELS WITH
+NO LINES CUT.
+
+USE:
+TYPE%SHOWCUT2+ON THE COMMAND LINE AND OPTIONAL TERSE PARM.
+
%COMMAND ===> SHOWCUT2 {TERSE}
+***************************** TOP OF DATA *****************************
%RESULT:
%==MSG>
%==MSG> CUT LEVEL 1 HAS 4 LINE(S)
%==MSG>          DATA LINE 1
%==MSG> CUT LEVEL 2 HAS 9 LINE(S)
%==MSG>          DATA LINE 1
%==MSG> NO LINE(S) CUT FOR LEVEL 3
%==MSG> CUT LEVEL 4 HAS 9 LINE(S)
%==MSG>          DATA LINE 1
%==MSG> NO LINE(S) CUT FOR LEVEL 5
)PROC
&KEY = .PFKEY
)END
